# Control-plane ownership — see #277.
#
# The factory merges product/app PRs autonomously (the human merge gate was removed
# 2026-06-07). But the factory must not be able to silently rewrite the workflows,
# agent definitions, RBAC, secrets, and architecture decisions that GOVERN it. These
# paths require review by a human/control-plane owner before merge.
#
# NOTE: CODEOWNERS only enforces review when branch protection has
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled on `main`. Enabling that branch-protection
# rule is the second half of #277 and must be done in repo settings.

# The factory's own control plane
/.github/                @ianreay
/.github/workflows/      @ianreay
/.github/agents/         @ianreay

# Deploy RBAC and cluster security posture
/deploy/k8s/             @ianreay
/charts/app/templates/   @ianreay

# Architecture decisions (immutable once accepted)
/docs/adrs/              @ianreay

# Secret-handling scripts
/scripts/seed-demo-users.sh @ianreay
